description:
Grand Canyon Disaster



Aired on 01/24/2013, Narrated by: Jonathan Aris



On 30 June 1956, United Airlines Flight 718, a Douglas DC-7, collides with Trans World Airlines Flight 2, a Lockheed L-1049 Super Constellation, over the Grand Canyon in Arizona. All 128 occupants on both flights are killed. At the time, it was the deadliest airline crash in history, and would lead to sweeping changes to flight operations rules over the United States.
